Mobile app development offers diverse career opportunities, especially in the local e-commerce space.

## Roles:
- **Flutter Developer**: Build cross-platform mobile apps.
- **Mobile UI/UX Designer**: Design intuitive interfaces for mobile users.
- **Backend Engineer**: Build APIs and services that power mobile apps.
- **QA Engineer**: Test mobile apps for bugs, usability, and performance.
- **Product Manager**: Define features and roadmap for mobile products.

## Internship at LocalWala:
Interns work on real mobile features, collaborate with senior engineers, and contribute to the LocalWala app used by thousands of users. Skills learned here are directly applicable to the mobile app industry.''', null, 10, 4)on conflict do nothing;-- Module 2 Lessons  ('20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000104', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000011', 'Dart Programming Basics', '# Dart Programming BasicsDart is the programming language behind Flutter. It is optimized for UI development and compiles to native code.## Core Syntax:   - **Variables**: `String name = ''''LocalWala'''';`- **Functions**: `void main() { print(''''Hello Flutter''''); }`- **Async/Await**: Handle API calls and local storage.- **Classes & Objects**: Model real-world entities like `Product`, `Order`, and `User`.## Example: Product Model```dartclass Product {  final String id;  final String name;  final double price;  final String imageUrl;  Product({required this.id, required this.name, required this.price, required this.imageUrl});}```, null, 10, 1),  ('20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000105', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000011', 'Flutter Widgets & Layout', '# Flutter Widgets & LayoutFlutter uses a declarative UI model where every element is a widget.## Essential Widgets:- **Scaffold**: Main app layout with appBar, body, and bottomNavigationBar.- **ListView / GridView**: Display lists of restaurants, products, or orders.- **Card**: Elevated containers for product items.- **TextFormField**: Input fields for search, addresses, and payments.## Building a Product Card:```dartCard(  child: ListTile()```, null, 10, 2),  ('20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000106', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000011', 'State Management in Flutter', '# State Management in FlutterState management determines how data flows through your app and updates the UI.## Approaches:- **setState**: Simple, built-in, ideal for small screens.- **Provider**: Lightweight, recommended for medium apps.- **Riverpod**: Modern, testable, and scalable.- **Bloc**: Enterprise-grade, separates business logic from UI.## LocalWala Example:A cart screen needs to reflect quantity changes instantly. Using Provider or Riverpod, the cart state updates automatically across screens without manual refresh.## Best Practice:, null, 10, 3),insert into academy_lessons (id, module_id, title, content_md, video_url, duration_minutes, order_no) values  ('20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000107', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000011

Flutter provides multiple ways to navigate between screens.

## Methods:
- **Navigator.push / pop**: Simple stack-based navigation.
- **Named Routes**: Define routes in MaterialApp for cleaner code.
- **GoRouter**: Declarative routing with deep linking support.

## LocalWala Navigation Flow:
- Home → Restaurant List → Menu → Cart → Checkout → Order Tracking
- Each screen pushes onto the stack, but some (like login) may replace the entire stack.

## Deep Linking Example:
A notification "Your order is ready" should open the Order Tracking screen directly, even if the app was closed. GoRouter handles this elegantly.''', null, 10, 4)on conflict do nothing;-- Module 3 Lessons  ('20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000108', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000012', 'Designing for Local E-Commerce', '# Designing for Local E-CommerceMobile UX for local commerce must prioritize speed, clarity, and trust.## Design Principles:- **Above-the-fold content**: Show restaurants, categories, and offers instantly.- **Visual hierarchy**: Use images, prices, and ratings prominently.- **One-thumb usability**: Place key actions (add to cart, checkout) within easy reach.- **Offline support**: Cache menus and cart for low-connectivity areas.## LocalWala Patterns:- Home screen with horizontal category scrolls and vertical restaurant list.- Bottom sheet for cart instead of full-screen cart for quick add/remove., null, 10, 1),  ('20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000109', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000012', 'Product Listings & Search', '# Product Listings & SearchEfficient product discovery drives conversions in local e-commerce.## Features:- **Search bar**: Real-time filtering by name, category, or restaurant.- **Filters**: Veg/non-veg, price range, rating, delivery time.- **List vs Grid**: Lists for restaurants, grids for product images.- **Infinite scroll**: Load more items as user scrolls.## Implementation Tips:- Debounce search input to avoid excessive API calls.- Cache search results locally for instant re-loads.- Show skeleton loaders while fetching data., null, 10, 2),  ('20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000110', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000012', 'Cart, Checkout & Payments', '# Cart, Checkout & PaymentsThe cart and checkout flow is where transactions happen.## Cart Logic:- Add/remove items with quantity tracking.- Persist cart in local storage (SharedPreferences or Hive).- Sync cart with backend when user logs in.## Checkout Flow:1. Review cart items and total.2. Select delivery address.3. Choose payment method: COD, UPI, card, wallet.4. Place order and receive confirmation with estimated delivery time.## Payment Integration:- Use Razorpay, PhonePe, or Paytm SDK for UPI and card payments.- Handle payment success, failure, and pending states gracefully., null, 10, 3),insert into academy_lessons (id, module_id, title, content_md, video_url, duration_minutes, order_no) values  ('20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000111', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000012

Keeping customers informed reduces anxiety and support tickets.

## Tracking Features:
- Real-time order status: confirmed → preparing → ready → out for delivery → delivered.
- Map view showing delivery partner location.
- Push notifications for status changes.

## Implementation:
- Use WebSocket or polling to fetch order status updates.
- Integrate Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) for push notifications.
- Show in-app notification banner even when app is open.

## LocalWala Approach:
Customers receive notifications at each milestone. Delivery partners also get real-time updates to optimize routes.''', null, 10, 4)on conflict do nothing;-- Module 4 Lessons  ('20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000112', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000013', 'App Architecture & Folder Structure', '# App Architecture & Folder StructureA scalable folder structure keeps your code maintainable as the app grows.## Recommended Structure:```lib/├── core/│   ├── constants/│   ├── theme/│   └── utils/├── data/│   ├── models/│   ├── repositories/│   └── services/├── features/│   ├── home/│   ├── cart/│   ├── orders/│   └── profile/├── routes/└── main.dart```## Layered Architecture:- **Presentation**: Widgets and screens.- **Domain**: Business logic and use cases.- **Data**: Repositories, models, and API services., null, 10, 1),  ('20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000113', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000013', 'Backend Integration & REST APIs', '# Backend Integration & REST APIsMobile apps need to communicate with servers to fetch and update data.## Key Concepts:- **REST APIs**: Standard HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE).- **Authentication**: JWT tokens stored securely and sent in request headers.- **Error Handling**: Gracefully handle 401, 403, 500 errors with retries.- **Offline Sync**: Queue requests when offline and process when online.## Example: Fetching Restaurants```dartFuture<List<Restaurant>> fetchRestaurants() async {  final response = await http.get(    headers: {''''Authorization'''': ''''Bearer \$token''''},  );  return (jsonDecode(response.body) as List)      .map((r) => Restaurant.fromJson(r))      .toList();}```, null, 10, 2),  ('20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000114', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000013', 'Local Storage & Caching', '# Local Storage & CachingMobile apps must work reliably even with poor connectivity.## Storage Options:- **SharedPreferences**: Key-value pairs for user preferences and tokens.- **Hive**: Fast, lightweight NoSQL database for offline carts and cached products.- **SQLite**: Structured storage for complex relational data.## Caching Strategy:- Cache restaurant menus and product lists for 15-30 minutes.- Store cart locally and sync with server when connection returns.- Use stale-while-revalidate pattern for optimal UX.## Example: Hive Box for Cart```dartvar box = Hive.box(''cart'');box.put(''items'', cartItems);```, null, 10, 3),insert into academy_lessons (id, module_id, title, content_md, video_url, duration_minutes, order_no) values  ('20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000115', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000013

A slow app loses users. Optimize for speed and smoothness.

## Techniques:
- **ListView.builder**: Build only visible items, not the entire list.
- **Cached Network Images**: Cache product images to avoid re-downloading.
- **Const widgets**: Mark static widgets as const to reduce rebuilds.
- **Isolates**: Offload heavy computations like JSON parsing.

## Metrics to Track:
- App launch time: target < 2 seconds.
- Screen transition: target < 300ms.
- API response: show skeleton loaders if > 500ms.

## LocalWala Optimization:
Product images are cached aggressively. Restaurant lists use pagination to render only 20 items at a time, keeping the UI responsive even on low-end devices.''', null, 10, 4)on conflict do nothing;-- Module 5 Lessons  ('20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000116', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000014', 'Testing Flutter Apps', '# Testing Flutter AppsTesting ensures your app works correctly and catches bugs before users do.## Test Types:- **Unit Tests**: Test individual functions and business logic.- **Widget Tests**: Verify UI renders correctly and responds to user input.- **Integration Tests**: Test complete user flows like placing an order.## Example: Widget Test```darttestWidgets(''''Add to cart button increments count'''', (WidgetTester tester) async {  await tester.pumpWidget(ProductScreen(product: product));  await tester.tap(find.byIcon(Icons.add_shopping_cart));  await tester.pump();  expect(find.text(''''1 in cart''''), findsOneWidget);});```## LocalWala Testing Focus:, null, 10, 1),  ('20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000117', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000014', 'Build & Deployment', '# Build & DeploymentDeploying a Flutter app involves building platform-specific binaries and publishing them.## Steps:1. **Configure app metadata**: name, bundle ID, icons, splash screens.2. **Build release APK/IPA**: `flutter build apk --release` or `flutter build ios --release`.3. **Test release build**: Install on physical devices to catch issues.4. **Publish**: Upload to Google Play Store and Apple App Store.## CI/CD:Use GitHub Actions or Codemagic to automate builds on every release.## Over-The-Air Updates:, null, 10, 2),  ('20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000118', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000014', 'LocalWala Ecosystem & Business Model', '# LocalWala Ecosystem & Business ModelUnderstanding the business helps you build better software.## Three-Sided Platform:- **Customers**: Browse, order, and track deliveries.- **Vendors**: Manage menus, accept orders, and track earnings.- **Delivery Partners**: Accept delivery requests and navigate routes.## Revenue Model:- Commission on each order.- Subscription plans for vendors.- Advertising and promotions.## Tech Stack at LocalWala:- **Mobile**: Flutter for customer app, native modules for delivery partner app.- **Backend**: Node.js / Go microservices.- **Database**: PostgreSQL for relational data, Redis for caching.- **Infrastructure**: AWS / GCP with CDN for static assets., null, 10, 3),  ('20000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000119', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000014', 'Preparing for LocalWala Internship', '# Preparing for LocalWala InternshipTurn your Flutter skills into a real-world internship.## What Interns Do:- Build features for the LocalWala customer or vendor app.- Fix bugs and improve performance.- Collaborate with designers, backend engineers, and product managers.- Participate in code reviews and agile sprints.## Skills LocalWala Looks For:- Solid Dart and Flutter fundamentals.- Understanding of REST APIs and state management.- Ability to write clean, testable code.- Good communication and teamwork.- Curiosity about local commerce and hyperlocal logistics.## Internship Project Ideas:1. Build a reusable Flutter widget library for LocalWala.2. Improve offline cart synchronization.3. Add analytics tracking for user behavior.4. Optimize image loading for slow networks.## Application Tips:- Complete this course and score well in the final assessment.- Build a small Flutter project and host it on GitHub.- Highlight any contributions to open-source Flutter packages.- Be ready to discuss how you would improve the LocalWala app.Good luck!'', null, 10, 4)on conflict do nothing;-- Quizzesinsert into academy_quizzes (id, module_id, title, passing_score, time_limit_minutes) values  ('30000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000010', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000010', 'Module 1 Quiz - Mobile Apps & Flutter', 50, 10),  ('30000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000011', '10000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000011', 'Mod